<div class="post-date">Dec 29</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1027" title="The big melt"> The big melt</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>Madison, Indiana, the most beautiful slush city in America.</p>

	<p>The &#8220;official&#8221; tally was 18-inches of snow in 24-hours. The total landed our county on the state&#8217;s emergency disaster aid list in the state. That might help pay the overtime of our diehard snow guys. They did an awesome job even working through Christmas, though they did take turns going home for periods to be with family.</p>

	<p>That subsequent freeze caused havoc on our town&#8217;s guttering. Buildings all across downtown had huge icicles hanging from the roof as the downspouts froze over.</p>

	<p>Across the street this morning, absolutely huge gutter-shaped chunks of ice came raining down on the sidewalk as the guttering collapsed.</p>

	<p>Another building had their windows cracked by cascading ice.</p>

	<p>At our library, a frozen downspout caused the melting snow and ice water to run down the side of the building and flooding into the children&#8217;s room. We got the books off the shelf largely in time, though we lost maybe 8 books. When I pulled one of the wet books off the shelf, it was entitled&#8212;&#8220;I Got Wet.&#8221;</p>

	<p>Go figure.</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

<div class="smallcat">Posted in <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?c=Madison">Madison</a></div>
<div class="smalluser"> by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a></div>
